  <h3>Manufacturing Facilities</h3>
  
  <p>Bajaj Auto operates state-of-the-art manufacturing plants in Chakan, Waluj (Aurangabad), and Pantnagar. The Akurdi plant in Pune houses the R&D center 'Ahead,' showcasing the company's commitment to research and development.</p>
  
  <h3>Product Range</h3>
  
  <p>From iconic motorcycles like the Bajaj Pulsar and Avenger to the world's largest fleet of auto-rickshaws, Bajaj offers a diverse product lineup. The company's innovative approach led to the creation of the low-cost car segment and marked its entry into electric scooters with the launch of the Chetak in January 2020.</p>
  
  <h3>Market Listing and Shareholding</h3>
  
  <p>Bajaj Auto's equity shares are listed on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) and the National Stock Exchange of India (NSE). As of December 31, 2022, the promoters, Bajaj Group, held 54.98% of the equity shares, reflecting strong support from various stakeholders.</p>
  
  <h3>Employee Engagement and Leadership</h3>
  
  <p>With a workforce of 10,000 employees as of 2019, Bajaj Auto emphasizes diversity, with 0.63% women and 0.31% differently-abled individuals. The company's leadership transitioned to Rajiv Bajaj, continuing the legacy of innovation and success.</p>
  
